"Missing Colors"
Watercolor on A3 200GSM
Inspired by @inkten
-
An illustration of Gumiho, a nine-tailed fox in Korean's tale which can turns into a woman to seduce men, then kills them by eating their hearts. I made this piece to represent her motivation behind her chaotic character. 
A man killed her cub in a winters day, and she feel very lost for that tragedy. She plans to get an easy revenge, by searching a power to turn into man's weakness, a woman. So she meditates for a thousand years and gets another 8 tails while in her meditation phase.

Fire (火 huǒ)
Earth (土 tǔ)
Metal (金 jīn)
Wood (木 mù)
and Water (水 shuǐ)

The nine of us(@frsindra, @b_stevan, @johannafebriany, @monicaariesta, @joannakrista, @purplevalen, @angelagrct, @ovitapp) are currently working on a project named #GEEKSKUADPROJECT or GSP in short which (hopefully) will soon be operational. The project was initiated last year when we did a colaboration work in anticipation of Marvel's Civil War and we found that we are all geeks on a certain level in our life. The project will cover arts (both original and fanarts) which mostly will revolve around comics and heroes. Please do support us by following our account @geekskuadproject . Your support will mean so much to each and everyone of us GSP members.
